      第 16 筆 ---------------------------------------------------------------------




系統識別號
U0026-1907201316184900


論文名稱(中文) 
      
南投縣觀光產業發展能源使用之研究


論文名稱(英文) 
      
The Energy Consumption Study on Tourism Industry Development in Nantou


校院名稱
成功大學


系所名稱(中)
都市計劃學系碩博士班


系所名稱(英)
Department of Urban Planning


學年度
101


學期
2


出版年
102


研究生(中文)
謝欣融


學號
P26001093


學位類別
碩士


語文別
中文


口試日期
2013-06-20


論文頁數
81頁


口試委員
口試委員-白仁德
口試委員-石豐宇
口試委員-張秀慈
指導教授-孔憲法



關鍵字(中)
投入產出生命週期評估觀光產業南投縣


關鍵字(英)
EIO-LCATourism IndustryNantou


學科別分類



中文摘要
觀光活動已成為全球性的重要經濟活動，觀光產業也成為各國積極發展的重要產業。從2000年到2010年，全球觀光旅遊人次6.8億成長到9.4億，全球觀光旅遊經濟也在全球GDP占了9.2%；臺灣的國內旅遊人次從7900萬成長到1.2億，GDP占約2.07%。但值得省思的是，因為觀光產業被認為是｢無煙囪產業｣，而使得觀光產業的環境議題未受到重視，與觀光產業相關的研究多從經濟面探討且肯定觀光產業對於地方經濟發展的重要性，其所產生的能源消耗及環境議題則較少被重視。本研究使用經RAS法推估之區域投入產出模型，分析民國95年南投縣觀光產業發展與其他產業的關聯效果，並結合經濟部能源局能源平衡表資料利用投入產出生命週期評估（Economic Input-Output Life-Cycle Assessment, EIO LCA）得到南投縣觀光產業發展之產值、能源密集度及二氧化碳排放量。研究結果顯示，在民國95年之南投縣產業結構，觀光產業產值約57.2億，占全縣生產總額2.45％，但其對於南投縣經濟發展之帶動、支持能力僅為平均水準。而觀光產業之能源密集度為4.6611，高於當年度商業部門整體之1.80；並產生25.678千公噸之CO2，人均排放0.0479公噸，密集度為0.004（公斤CO2/元）


英文摘要
Tourist activity has played an important role in global economic activity, and tourism industry has been the important industry that many countries make effort to develop. According to the World Tourism Organization (UNWTO), international arrivals worldwide have risen from 675 million in 2000 to 940 million in 2010, and tourism industry contributes 9% of global gross domestic product (GDP). In Taiwan, domestic travel increase from 79 million in 2000 to 120 million in 2010, and tourism industry contributes 4.7% of GDP. On the contrary, the environment issue of tourism industry has not yet been recognized since it’s known as an “industry without chimney.” Most researches about tourism industry are concern with the economic growth and approve that tourism industry is important to local economic development, But seldom discuss the relation between tourism industry, energy consumption and environment issue.In this research we use the regional input-output table which estimated by RAS procedures to analysis linkage effect between tourism industry and other industries in Nantou County, 2006. And we compute the tourism industry value, energy intensity and CO2 discharge by using Economic Input-Output Life-Cycle Assessment (EIO-LCA).The result shows that the tourism industry development in Nantou County generated NT$ 5.72 billion which is 2.45% of the total value. The energy intensity of tourism industry is 4.661 which higher than business sector in 2006 and the CO2 discharge 25.678 thousand tonne and the intensity of carbon dioxide is 0.004 (kg/TWD).


論文目次
